                    </div>
                    <span>This book is almost a perfect solution for an introductory AI class, since it presents the chapters on both Prolog and LISP programming. The introduction to those languages is rather detailed, the Prolog chapter takes up about 75 pages while LISP introduction is almost 100 pages long. Without focusing on any particular subject in AI the book tends to be substantial and detailed.</span>
                  
              
